nio/GoogleOauth.Output:
An output signal of the queried analytics data. Details of the Google Analytics data can be found [here](https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/reporting/core/v3/reference#data_response). The following is a sample of commonly included attributes, but note that not all will be included on every signal:
* kind
* id
* query
- start-date
- end-date
- ids
- filters
- start-index
- max-results
* itemsPerPage
* totalResults
* previousLink
* nextLink
* profileInfo
- profileId
- accountId
- profileName
* columnHeaders
- name
- columnType
* rows

Reauthenticate Interval.description: time in between authentications with Google

nio/GoogleOauth.Description: Collect data from Google Analytics and output to a signal.
